# git add
when changes have been made inside a git repository that yoy want to keep , you will need to use ' git add'command
items that have not been "tracked" before will start to be tracked and all other changes will be marcked as modified.
generally, you can get away the command'git add' which all files and directories that were added , changed , or deleted .
you can track changes to specific files using 'gitt add file1 file2' which all track specfically file1 and and file2.
you can specify tracking directories with ' git add directoryName.
